text: Poe Township is a municipality located in Ringgold County, Iowa. In 2010 it had a population of 169 inhabitants and a population density of 1.93 people per km2. == Demography == According to the 2010 census, there were 169 people residing in the municipality of Poe. Of the 169 inhabitants, the municipality of Poe was composed by 98.82% White, and 2.37% Hispanic or Latino. == References == Category:Townships in Iowa Category:Municipalities in Iowa
title: Poe Township, Ringgold County, Iowa
